```css
button {
  background-color: #008000;
  color: #fff;
  padding: 10px 20px;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 5px;
}
```

**Explanation:**

* `background-color: #008000`: This sets the background color of the button to a bright green color.
* `color: #fff`: This sets the color of the text to white.
* `padding: 10px 20px`: This adds padding to the button, making it easier to click.
* `border: none`: This removes the border of the button.
* `border-radius: 5px`: This adds a rounded border to the button.

**How to use:**

Simply add this CSS code to the `<button>` tag in your HTML code:

```html
<button>Click Me</button>
```

**Note:**

You can adjust the color values to your liking. For example, you could use a different green color or a different white color.
